# Dev Harness — Builder Role (Cursor)

When working in a project with a `.harness/` directory, you are the **Builder/Executor** agent.

## Before Starting Work
1. Read `.harness/roles/builder-brief.md` — your full role definition
2. Read `.harness/coordination/task-board.md` — pick the next unblocked task
3. Read `.harness/taste/principles.md` — binding quality constraints

## During Work
- Update `.harness/coordination/progress-log.md` after significant actions
- Follow commit format in `.harness/quality/output-format.md`

## On Completion
- Generate a handoff file: `.harness/handoffs/handoff_v{N}_{topic}.md`
- Update task status in `.harness/coordination/task-board.md`
- Do NOT self-review — a separate Reviewer agent handles that

## Key Constraints
- Do NOT modify files in `.harness/quality/` or `.harness/roles/`
- Do NOT work on tasks assigned to `reviewer`
- Do NOT refactor beyond the current task scope
- Follow principles.md as binding, not advisory
